# Implementation Plan — PRISM Dashboard Monolith Decomposition (Phase F5)

## Executive Summary

The PRISM SOTA Operator Dashboard currently relies on [dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts) as a central hub. Over successive development iterations, this file has evolved into a colossal vertical monolith (~528 KiB, over 9,800 lines of code) incorporating:
1.  **Low-level Node HTTP/HTTPS servers** and WebSocket routing.
2.  **Telemetry algorithms** (percentile histogram calculation, self-healing diagnostic triggers, correlation tracking).
3.  **Active swarms & agents orchestration** loops.
4.  **Session packages compilation** and SQLite exporter frameworks.
5.  **Inline HTML serving and static assets templates**.

This monolith concentrates system risks: an error in a telemetry plotting endpoint can crash the master WebSocket connection, destabilizing ongoing agent runs.

This plan details the **Phase F5 Decomposition Solution**, breaking down the monolith into a lightweight controller shell and cleanly decoupled, domain-specific services and sub-routers, keeping all generated modules **strictly under the 120 KiB threshold**.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Because the dashboard serves as the central runtime coordinator, any modularization must preserve:
> 1.  **WebSocket Handshakes**: Ongoing terminal sessions, framebuffer streams, and console logs must experience zero interruption.
> 2.  **API Version Parity**: Public/internal endpoints served at `/api/v1/*` must keep exact parameter shapes to prevent breaking the operator TUI or the upcoming Python SDK.
> 3.  **Core Performance**: Latencies of the decoupled policy and telemetry paths must remain below strict CI thresholds ($\le$ 50ms and $\le$ 30ms, respectively).

---

## Proposed Changes

We will restructure the operator module by introducing a clean **Services & Routers** architectural boundary. The code will be grouped logically into decoupled subsystems.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Dashboard[dashboard-service.ts: HTTP/WS Controller Shell] --> Router[Router Pipeline]
    Router --> ChatRouter[routes/chat.ts]
    Router --> TelemetryRouter[routes/telemetry.ts]
    Router --> PackageRouter[routes/packages.ts]
    Router --> SystemRouter[routes/system.ts]

    ChatRouter --> ChatService[services/chat-service.ts]
    TelemetryRouter --> TelemetryService[services/telemetry-service.ts]
    PackageRouter --> PackageService[services/package-service.ts]
```

### Component: Core Business Services (`/src/core/operator/services/`)
We will extract high-computational algorithms and state storage definitions from the monolith into independent, unit-testable services.

#### [NEW] [telemetry-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/services/telemetry-service.ts)
*   **Role**: Computes windowed telemetry, trace correlation indexing, and self-healing recommendation rules.
*   *Size Target*: ~45 KiB.

#### [NEW] [slo-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/services/slo-service.ts)
*   **Role**: Extracts linear interpolation percentile logic (`histogramPercentile()`) and matches Prometheus metric observations against `SLO_TARGETS`.
*   *Size Target*: ~25 KiB.

#### [NEW] [package-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/services/package-service.ts)
*   **Role**: Compiles session package envelopes, aggregates historic timeline transition logs, and coordinates trace export packaging.
*   *Size Target*: ~55 KiB.

#### [NEW] [chat-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/services/chat-service.ts)
*   **Role**: Standardizes completions triggers, model provider registrations, key slot assignments, and executor run environments.
*   *Size Target*: ~60 KiB.

